text.tspan: Location tracking
Use a GPS watch or smartphone app like Strava
or Nike Run Club to track location, distance, and
pace. Consider popular options like Garmin
Forerunner or Polar Vantage.
Water bottle
Stay hydrated during long runs with a hydration
belt or handheld bottle like the Nathan
SpeedDraw Plus.
Lightning
Wear reflective gear like a vest or accessory to
stay visible during low-light runs. Options
include the Amphipod Xinglet or Noxgear
Tracer360.
Snacks
Grab fresh fruit like bananas, apples, or oranges
for pre-workout snacks. For a post-workout
boost, consider energy bars like Clif Bars or KIND
bars.
Heart Rate
Track heart rate with a monitor or smartwatch
like Apple Watch or Fitbit. Popular heart rate
monitors include the Polar H10 and Wahoo
TICKR.
Timer
Use a smartwatch with a timer function like
Apple Watch or Garmin Forerunner to track
workout time and pace.
Essential Items to
Enhance Your
Runs

tspan.tspan: - Avoid disrupting other runners by running side by side, stretching or chatting too close to the track.
- Use the changing rooms to avoid bringing winter clothes or outdoor shoes onto the track, as they may damage the - surface.
- Strollers are allowed on the track but not recommended during peak hours at lunchtime and in the evening. Peak hours may vary depending on the season.
- Spitting on the track and in the stadium is prohibited
